Package: wisegroup
Title: Safe grouping wrappers for group-aware tidy functions
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R: 
    c(person(given = "Miles",
           family = "McBain",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "miles.mcbain@gmail.com",
           comment = c(ORCID = "YOUR-ORCID-ID")),
      person(given = "RStudio",
             role = "cph"),
      person(given = "Hadley",
             family = "Wickham",
             role = c("cph"),
             email = "hadley@rstudio.com"))
Description: Group-safe versions of tidyverse functions that either
             automatically ungroup the returned data, or explicity indicate that
             the returned data could be grouped in source code. This helps avoid
             errors relating to forgetting call dplyr's ungroup().
License: MIT + file LICENSE
